'''John Francis Doerfler''' (born November 2, 1964) is an American [[Roman Catholic]] [[bishop]]. He serves as the head of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Marquette|Marquette, Michigan diocese]].

==Personal life==
Doerfler was born to Henry and Germaine Mancl Doerfler in [[Appleton, Wisconsin]].

==Education==
He attended [[Appleton West High School]] and graduated in 1983. He earned a  B.A. in Philosophy and Classics at the [[College of St. Thomas]] in [[St. Paul, Minnesota]] in 1987. He entered the seminary and was sent to the [[Pontifical Gregorian University]] in Rome where he earned a Bachelor of Sacred Theology (S.T.B.) in 1990. In 1987, he was awarded a Licentiate in Canon Law (J.C.L.) from the [[Catholic University of America]]. He continued his studies at the [[John Paul II Institute for Marriage and the Family]] on the campus of the Catholic University of America receiving his Licentiate (S.T.L) and Doctorate (S.T.D) in Sacred Theology (1999 and 2008).<ref name="The Compass">{{cite news|last=Sam|first=Lucero|title=Diocese bids Bishop-elect Doerfler farewell at Mass, dinner Jan. 19|url=http://www.thecompassnews.org/2014/01/diocese-bids-bishop-elect-doerfler-farewell-mass-dinner-jan-19/|accessdate=February 13, 2014|newspaper=The Compass (official newspaper of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Green Bay]])|date=January 24, 2014}}</ref> 

==Priesthood==
On June 31, 1991, he was ordained a priest for the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Green Bay]], [[Wisconsin]]. He was named as a [[coadjutor bishop]] on February 11, 2000 for the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Cheyenne]].<ref name="The Compass" /> He followed Cheyenne's Bishop [[David Ricken]] back to the Green Bay diocese in 2001 and eventually served as the [[vicar general]].<ref name="The Compass" />  On December 17, 2013, [[Pope Francis]] appointed Doerfler as the bishop of the [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Marquette]], [[Michigan]]. He was installed as the diocese's thirteenth bishop on February 11, 2014.<ref>[http://www.dioceseofmarquette.org/newsrelease_view.php?page=109 Green Bay Priest Appointed Bishop of Marquette]</ref><ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bdoerf.html Bishop John Francis Doerfler]</ref>

